observations.recommendation:
We Recommended that Management direct the

a. City Disaster Risk Reduction Management Office (CDRRMO) to submit the Report on sources and Utilization of DRRMF to the Audit Team on or before the 15th day after the end of each month for verification and review;

b. City Accounting and Internal Audit Office to revisit the existing process flows and policies to determine the necessary enhancements particularly in the area of utilization of cash donations and to monitor compliance thereto. Moreover, together with the City General Services Office, prepare and submit the mandatory reports for the cash donations and donated relief goods and compliance with the provision of COA Circular No. 2014-002 dated April 25, 2014;

c. City Treasurer to cause the transfer of the CY 2017 unutilized balance from the Special Trust Fund to General Fund; and

d. City Administrator’s Office, City Treasurer’s Office, CDRRMO, and City Health Office to properly coordinate for the planning and utilization of the cash donations granted to the City Government.

We recommended and the LCE agreed to instruct the concerned departments to – 

(a) conduct a thorough planning for the implementation of development projects; 
(b) consider the appropriate timing and phasing of their implementation; and


(c) monitor the effectiveness and efficient implementation of the projects under the 20% DF so that the necessary and timely intervention can be made to ensure the timeliness of the implementation of the programmed projects;
